{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2922j","heading":"Annual report on purchase of drop-in fuel","label":"2922j Annual report on purchase of drop-in fuel","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptIV/ch173/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identifies each instance in which the Secretary purchased drop-in fuel that was not cost-competitive with traditional fuel; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for each instance identified under paragraph (1), states whether the purchase was based on a military requirement or not.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Definitions","label":"b .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “drop-in fuel” means a neat or blended liquid hydrocarbon fuel designed as a direct replacement for a traditional fuel with comparable performance characteristics and compatible with existing infrastructure and equipment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2922j/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs2922j%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “traditional fuel” means a liquid hydrocarbon fuel derived or refined from petroleum.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
